node.text:
Sexism with @tova_leigh ☝️

"A few weeks ago I asked you to share with me examples of sexism & casual sexism in your lives. I was inundated by thousands of messages from, mainly women, who shared from their everyday lives examples of sexism and how it affects them. It’s been on my mind ever since... Sexism affects everyone, including men... But the reason I wanted to make this video is because there is a very strong link between sexism and gender inequality and I truly believe that until we break these stereotypes we’ve all been brainwashed to believe, we will struggle to achieve true equality."

Video by @tova_leigh, shared with permission. For more videos like these head over to Tova's page 🙌

#sexism #casualsexism #sexist #inequality #equality #equalpay #misogny #patriarchy #tovaleigh #feminist #feminism #kindness #youmatter #worth #selfworth #believe #empowerment #InspirationalWomen #inspirational #protest #positivevibes #positivity #heforshe #achieve #support #instagood #lesson

A powerful poem by @holliepoetry

"Why is titillation accepted and sustenance rejected?"

This video was directed by Jake Dypka @dypka with Indy 8 for Channel 4 Random Acts with help from hundreds up people via a KickStarter campaign. Video shared with permission.

Find out more about Hollie in this week's episode of The Female Lead's podcast. Listen now: link in bio.

node.text:
Meet Kathrine Switzer @kathrineswitzer, the first woman to officially enter The Boston Marathon. Despite being attacked by an official she finished the race and became an activist for women around the world successfully lobbying for the women's marathon to become an Olympic sport 🏃‍♀️

Find out more about Kathrine's work at @261fearless (give them a follow) 🙌❤

What is getting in the way of your success and your ability to move forward?

Hear Nada's story and join us at The Rise Leadership Course: https://lnkd.in/dxamEn6 (swipe up in stories or go to our website)

We have come together with Rise Up For You, SHRM-CP, SHRM-SCP to bring you a course designed to take you to the next level. From communication & assertiveness to emotional intelligence, negotiation skills and navigating unconscious bias - now is your chance to step up and invest in yourself.

The course started on the 5th of April but for anyone who missed the early signup, you will be sent the materials and playbacks. The second session is on the 19th so join before then: https://lnkd.in/dGSj5T9, to benefit from a LIVE session with a Q&A and audience coaching.

Rise Up For You are a proud supporter of The Female Lead

"In the three short months of 2021, I’ve had more difficult conversations with my kids than I ever had with my own parents.

It breaks my heart to have them, and I don’t know what the right way is, except to falter and and be awkward, and try to process together. My fellow Asian American parents, I’m grieving and standing with you today. Let us better equip our kids for the world they will inherit and shape." 

Video by @janeparkang, shared with permission ❤

#stopasianhate #hateisavirus #stophate

For the first time in history the VP is a woman. Madame Vice President Kamalujah, vice president 🎵 

Put your volume right up because @missymodell is back with another empowering parody 😁

"It only felt fitting to take today to celebrate the FIRST (but not the last!) female, Black, and South Asian Vice President in history 🎉 @vp 

Thank you Madame VP for making it all feel really possible - and a Happy #InternationalWomensDay to all of you brilliant, courageous, and resilient humans 💙

Written with @scottsimonsmusic 
Vocal mix & vocal mix: @mattbeilis 
Video edited by @pronouncedjan 
*Extremely* special thanks to @thecwolf

node.text:
Watch our LIVE panel with Raya and The Last Dragon's incredible female filmmakers including:

Producer: Osnat Shurer (also worked on Moana)
Screenwriter: Adele Lim (Crazy Rich Asians)
Head of Story: Fawn Veerasunthorn (Frozen)
Modeler: Liza Rhea (Ralph Breaks the Internet)

We talk about what it was like to work on the first Disney film made entirely from home, careers in the creative industry, the impact of COVID, representation of women in behind-the-scenes roles & the importance of diverse female role models.

Joined by the lovely 6-year-old Kiara and 14 year old @inspiringvanessa who ask some of the questions. The panel is be moderated by Katie Carroll!

Raya and The Last Dragon came out today on Disney Plus with Premiere Access, check it out 😃

node.text:
6-year-old Kiara surprises Awkwafina and Kelly Marie Tran with a special interview for their new film Disney's Raya and The Last Dragon.

We loved working with Disney for this and would like to invite you to join us for a special LIVE panel with Disney's Raya and The Last Dragon's incredible female filmmakers:

Producer: Osnat Shurer (also worked on Moana)
Screenwriter: Adele Lim (Crazy Rich Asians)
Head of Story: Fawn Veerasunthorn (Frozen)
Modeler: Liza Rhea (Ralph Breaks the Internet)

We will also be joined by The Female Lead's Founder Edwina Dunn, two young fans (who will be asking questions) 14-year-old Inspiring Vanessa @inspiringvanessa, 6-year-old Kiara who is in this video (thanks to her parents @mrsnydcrawford, @ryanashcrawford) and our wonderful moderator, Katie Carroll!

Also, stay tuned for a special message from the voice cast Awkwafina and Kelly Marie Tran and remember you can watch Raya and The Last Dragon from tomorrow on Disney+ Premier Access!

We'll be going LIVE at 6PM GMT 😁

node.text:
"I find it revealing when people mock where I came from, & say they’re going to “send me back to waitressing,” as if that is bad or shameful.

It’s as though they think being a member of Congress makes you intrinsically “better” than a waitress.

But our job is to serve, not rule."

MELINDAGAS ENG UIRE This year's 50 BEST & WORST WHO? BEACH BODIES THE GOOD, THE BAD THE UGLY! SHE'S39 E'S59 Hayley auditions KATE HUDSON TOM CRUISE BRIDE MARRIAGE BOOT CAMP! SEE INSIDE! node.text:
@alexlight_ldn: "I cried when I read this feature. Hot, angry tears. Not for myself, but for the millions of women - and men - who are going to see this and make judgements about their own body accordingly. ‘What would they say about mine?’, is a common thought after reading this, I imagine. 

This cover and this feature looks like it was published at least 10 years ago. When somebody sent it to me, I assumed it was. HOW can this horrendous, fatphobic, body shaming nonsense be allowed to go to press - and then appear on newsstands across the world? I’m baffled and angry - I genuinely thought ‘best and worst beach bodies’ features were a thing of the past. I didn’t believe anything as overt as this would even be considered in 2021. 

You might think I’m making a big deal out of a magazine feature - but I’m not. This is so, so harmful. And goes a great way to undoing all of the work people are doing to shatter diet culture and this current belief system we have whereby looks are valued above all else.

It tells people: ‘look ‘perfect’ or your body isn’t good enough’. Deserves shame and being dissected in an international publication. 

Anyway. I tried to fix one of the pages - swipe - to hopefully leave on a bit of a better note.."

Words by @alexlight_ldn

Final slide is @tessholliday's perfect response 👏
